cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use M-AIDA in academic work, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "M-AIDA: Meta-Analysis Intelligent Data Assistant"
version: 7.0.0
abstract: >-
  M-AIDA is a knowledge-driven, human-in-the-loop research software for
  extracting effect sizes from primary studies for meta-analysis in
  international business, specifically the internationalization–performance
  (I–P) relationship. A large-language-model pipeline produces draft
  extractions with confidence scores and converts t / F / beta statistics to
  Pearson r (Borenstein et al., 2009; Peterson & Brown, 2005); every record
  must be verified and overridden as needed by a Principal Investigator and
  then irreversibly locked (audit trail) before it can enter the analysis
  dataset. Automation reduces extraction time; the human investigator
  guarantees validity. Built on the authors' meta-analysis methodology and the
  dissertation's ICRV / cDAI / DPL moderator framework.
authors:
